@node Entities
@section Entities

Instead of working with raw data (Lisp association lists), it is also possible to work with wrapping CLOS objects, available in the ODATA/ENTITY package.

Use @code{T} as parameter to @code{fetch}. Instead of association lists, we get @code{ENTITY} objects:


@lisp
(-> +trip-pin-modify+
    (collection "People")
    (fetch t))
@end lisp

@example
#<http://services.odata.org/V4/(S(4olvgljic51nt3x0pqp5mpbl))/TripPinServiceRW/$metadata#People>
@end example


The elements of an entity set can be accessed with @code{ODATA/ENTITY:ENTITY-SET-ELEMENTS}:

@lisp
(-> +trip-pin-modify+
    (collection "People")
    (fetch t)
    (odata/entity:entity-set-elements))
@end lisp

